{
  "customInstructions": "Strictly follow these rules to save my budget and keep code clean:\n\n1. ARCHITECTURE: Vertical Slice Architecture ONLY. No layers-wide leaks.\n2. DRY 2.0: If any logic/value used >1 time in a file -> extract to local helper. If used in >1 file -> extract to shared helper/util.\n3. TESTING STRATEGY: \n   - Edge Cases FIRST (null, empty, errors, limits).\n   - Happy Path LAST.\n   - Mandatory 100% Line & Branch coverage.\n   - Every single line must be executed and asserted.\n4. TEST QUALITY:\n   - Use BUILDER PATTERN for all instances/mocks. No manual object literals.\n   - Minimal boilerplate: use abstractions for setup.\n   - Mutation-resistant assertions: strict equality, no 'toBeDefined' if value can be checked.\n5. PERFORMANCE: Do not index 'node_modules'. Avoid deep scans if not requested. Minimize output verbosity."
}